Provisioning a New Azure SQL Database Server Using PowerShell
=============================================================
This article shows you how to create Azure SQL Database services using Azure PowerShell.


Prerequisites
---------------------
Before you begin this tutorial, you must have the following:
* Azure Subscription, if you don't already have an Azure subscription, create a free account.
* Azure Data Studio(ADS) with PowerShell Extension, in this tutorial, we will used ADS to edit and run PowerShell scripts, see How to use PowerShell in Azure Data Studio.
https://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/resources/videos/azure-friday-how-to-use-powershell-in-azure-data-studio/#time=00h04m45s


* Provisioning a New Microsoft Azure SQL Database Server
* Configuring a firewall rule for a Microsoft Azure SQL Database Server
* Connecting to a Microsoft Azure SQL Database Server with PowerShell


Steps:
Before you begin this tutorial, authenticate your Azure subscription. then start the creation process. as follows.      






az group create --name "demo-rg" --location "NorthEurope"


#Creating a SERVER
az sql Server create \
--name "azcloudstkserver" \
--resource-group "demo-rg"\
--location easteu \
--admin-user "cloudstkadm" \
--admin-password "sfdf$"

Creating a Database
In this example, we will create a database called 'cloudstkdb'
az sql db create --resource-group "demo-rg" --server "azcloudstkserver" --name "cloudstkdb" \
